widgets_values:
Using CFG 1 will increase speed by 2x but will ignore negative prompt and decrease quality.
We are chaining two samplers to be able to use high cfg at start for quality and low cfg at end for speed.

nodes.title: Optional Fastwan Lora
widgets_values:
FASTWAN LORA

Download diffusion_pytorch_model.safetensors and place in /models/loras/
Rename to FastWan2.2-TI2V-5B.safetensors

https://huggingface.co/FastVideo/FastWan2.2-TI2V-5B-FullAttn-Diffusers/tree/main/transformer

Number of frames will be adapted to the closest number Wan supports.
Theoretically no upper limit. Will be limited as your graphics card goes out of memory.
Total steps will set the maximum number of steps. It will then calculate 50% of those steps to be split into high cfg and low cfg sampler, to increase speed by 30%+.
Quality of life feature where filename automatically adds pixel size and puts into desired folder.

WAN MODEL
wan2.2_ti2v_5B_fp16.safetensors
Model Manager
Search for the model in the model manager and press install

TEXT ENCODER
umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.safetensors
Download and place in your /models/text_encoders/ folder
https://huggingface.co/Kijai/WanVideo_comfy/resolve/main/umt5-xxl-enc-bf16.safetensors?download=true

VAE
wan2.2_vae.safetensors
Download and place in your /models/vae/ folder
https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Wan_2.2_ComfyUI_Repackaged/resolve/main/split_files/vae/wan2.2_vae.safetensors

If you're having triton, python, xformers, sageattn or similar errors, just dump the log into ChatGPT and it'll tell you how to install the correct versions you need.

If you are lacking in vram (GB memory of your graphics card) you can enable block swap. This will lower vram requirements but increase generation time.
Uses 14gb default for me.
Around 10gb with block swap.
